AB  - This paper introduces a class of bounded-influence estimators for the Gaussian censored-regression or Tobit model. These estimators can be interpreted as weighted ML estimators, with weights chosen to attain the best trade-off between efficiency and robustness. An empirical example illustrates the feasibility and usefulness of these estimators, as well as their performance vis-à-vis the Tobit ML, CLAD, and SCLS estimators.
